# OT Sentinel — Known IEC 104 IOA Values CDB List
# ================================================
# Format: IOA_VALUE:Description
#
# Used by rule 200029 (OT-SENTINEL-IEC-006) to detect ASDU messages
# referencing Information Object Addresses (IOAs) not previously observed.
#
# IOA values are 24-bit (0-16777215) and identify specific data points
# within a device. New/unknown IOAs may indicate ASDU spoofing or injection.
#
# Tuning:
# - Start empty for discovery mode (all IOAs alert once)
# - Add each legitimate IOA as it's observed during learning period
# - After learning period, only anomalous IOAs will alert
#
# Deployment: Copy to /var/ossec/etc/lists/ and add to ossec.conf:
#   <list>etc/lists/known_iec104_ioas</list>

# ===== ADD KNOWN IOA VALUES BELOW =====
# Format: IOA:Description
# Example: 100:Circuit_Breaker_1_Status
